<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-09-08T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-09-08T13:00:00-05:00" n="66" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d66">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">715.1715/574: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Cramp</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tegucigalpa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-09-08T12:00:00-06:00">September 8, 1937—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 5:13
                                    p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>57. For Duggan. Referring to our conversation this morning, I have
                                suggested to Castleman that he obtain some statement from President
                                Somoza with reference to his desire for reciprocal withdrawal of the
                                stamps, which could be quoted direct to the President of Honduras
                                tomorrow.</p>
                            <closer><signed>[<hi rend="smallcaps">Cramp</hi>]</signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>